news.title: U.S. housing starts, permits tumble in September
news.para: Housing starts dropped 1.6% to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 1.555 million units last month, the Commerce Department said on Tuesday. Data for August was revised down to a rate of 1.580 million units from the previously reported 1.615 million units.

news.title: ACC's net profit increases 24% at Rs 450.21 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: The company's total income stood at Rs 3,812.31 crore in Q2 FY22, a increase of 6 per cent from Rs 3,582.82 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Ekta World, Pashmina Realty lock horns over Rs 1,000-crore project in Mumbai
news.para: Ekta files FIR accusing Pashmina, promoters of fraud; Pashmina denies allegations, to seek legal recourse.

news.title: Jaipur civic body identifies 595 urban development tax defaulters
news.para: As per the orders, a person whose UD tax is about Rs 1 lakh a year or a person whose total default amount over the years for UD tax is around Rs 10 lakh, has to be taken up on priority.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body sends 1,000 notices to property tax defaulters
news.para: Although some people have been depositing the tax — the MC has earned over Rs 45 crore — the number of the defaulters is large. The authority has already sealed 15 commercial properties across the city. Some of these properties had been opened after payment of tax.

news.title: IndiQube sets up 1.5-lakh-sq-ft co-working center in Pune's Yerwada
news.para: The new co-working hub, spread across six floors in a standalone building, is the company’s eighth property in the city. With this, the company’s portfolio has risen to 10,000 seats across an area of 0.5 million sq ft in Pune alone.

news.title: Goa: Bill proposes six-month jail for no tenant verification
news.para: The bill puts the onus on house owners to verify the bonafides and inspect the photo identity of tenants before providing them accommodation. The photo identity could be any government-issued document — election card, driving licence, Aadhaar card, etc.

news.title: HeidelbergCement India's profit dips 4.55% to Rs 59.56 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: In a separate filing, HeidelbergCement India said its independent director/chairperson Akila Krishnakumar has resigned from the position and the board has accepted her resignation

news.title: Kolkata civic body kicks off drive to raze rickety buildings around Burrabazar
news.para: According to a KMC buildings department official, the drive is being conducted largely in the areas like Cotton Street, Rabindra Sarani, MG Road, Ahiritolla that are located in and around the Burrabazar belt.

news.title: K-RERA makes it mandatory for builders to disclose water sources during registration
news.para: Builders need to register residential projects with K-RERA with all the documents related to the project, which must be submitted online. After examining all these documents, a K- RERA registration number will be issued to them – known as a K-RERA approval.

news.title: Rajasthan: Against target of 32,000, only 1,000 lease deeds issued
news.para: Terming the section 69A of the Act ‘magical and game-changer’ in issuing lease deeds to old settlements under its ambitious ‘Prashasan Shehron ke Sang’ campaign, state government had set a target to issue 70% of the total lease deeds by using the section 69A.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body uses GIS to assess property tax
news.para: A Pimpri Chinchwad Municipal Corporation (PCMC) official said the Geographical Information System (GIS)-based survey would ensure transparency in tax collection and plug the leaks in revenue.

news.title: Nashik civic body's property tax amnesty scheme gets poor response
news.para: During the same period, the civic body has given a rebate of Rs 3 crore on penalty amount. The total property tax dues are estimated at Rs 279 crore, including Rs 104 crore basic tax and Rs 175 crore as penalty.

news.title: J&K administration inks MoU with Dubai government for real estate development
news.para: “This MoU is a milestone after which investment will pour in from entire globe and is a big developmental push. Different entities from Dubai have shown keen interest in investment,” an official statement quoting commerce and industry minister Piyush Goyal said.

news.title: Plots on offer for malls & shopping plazas in Greater Noida
news.para: The plots range from 2,500 to 12,000 square metres and are being offered at four times FAR (floor area ratio) for Rs 60,000 to Rs 66,000 per sqm.
